    <div class="note">
        💡 <strong>Key Takeaways:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Annotations provide metadata to Java code.</li>
            <li>Built‑in annotations (<code>@Override</code>, <code>@SuppressWarnings</code>, <code>@Deprecated</code>) help the compiler and developers.</li>
            <li>Custom annotations use <code>@interface</code> and can have methods (annotation elements).</li>
            <li>Meta‑annotations (<code>@Target</code>, <code>@Retention</code>, etc.) control where and how annotations are used.</li>
            <li>Annotations retained at runtime can be accessed via reflection.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

